An Act relative to outdoor heritage.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Section 58 of chapter 131 of the General Laws, as appearing in the 2022
2 official edition, is hereby amended by inserting, in line 6, after the word "thereof" the following
3 words:- , provided that a person may hunt with a bow and arrow from an elevated tree stand not
4 less than 250 feet from any dwelling in use except as authorized by the owner or occupant
5 thereof
6 SECTION 2. Section 64 of chapter 131 of the General Laws, as appearing in the 2022
7 official edition, is hereby amended by striking out, in lines 2 and 3, the words “, or any
8 crossbow, except as provided in section 69, nor” and inserting in place thereof the following the
9 word:- nor.
1 of 2

10 SECTION 3. Said chapter 131 is hereby further amended by striking out section 69, as so
11 appearing, and inserting in place thereof the following section:- Section 69. A person shall not
12 carry or use a bow and arrow or crossbow while hunting unless the bow and arrow or crossbow
13 meet the requirements of the rules and regulations which shall be promulgated by the director.
14 Such rules and regulations shall prescribe general design, weight of pull and type of bows and
15 arrows or crossbows and shall conform to standards generally accepted for hunting purposes.
16 SECTION 4. Section 5 of chapter 131 of the General Laws, as appearing in the 2022
17 official edition, is hereby amended by inserting after the second paragraph the following
18 paragraph:- The hunting of deer by bow and arrow shall be permitted on any date, including a
19 Sunday or legal holiday, that the director declares as an open season for such hunting. Except as
20 otherwise provided in the preceding paragraph, an open season declared by the director for the
21 hunting of deer by bow and arrow, which open season period occurs in whole or in part, within
22 the last 3 months of the calendar year, shall be for a period of not less than 7 days that shall be
23 consecutive.
24 SECTION 5. Section 57 of said chapter 131, as so appearing, is hereby amended by
25 inserting at the end of the paragraph the following sentence:- Notwithstanding, this section shall
26 not prohibit or render unlawful, the hunting of deer by bow and arrow or the carrying on his
27 person a bow and arrow for the purpose of hunting deer, during any Sunday declared as an open
28 season for such hunting, by the director with the approval of the fisheries and wildlife board.
